{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":13683,"record_hash":"sha256:7ec5c487a47864cec5f742de384fd3fd5f797bef05243c848bdd1f4a220c7bb4","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:05:22.403Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes. The biggest extra thing is: **`meta:local:*` will not satisfy the transport/sharing use cases by itself.**\n\nThat is good for the POC because it is safer, but long term we probably need two layers:\n\n```text\nlocal capture\n  meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:...\n  richer, private, raw-ish, redacted best-effort\n\nshareable/exported session\n  publishable GitMeta namespace or generated artifact\n  intentionally redacted, normalized, maybe summarized\n```\n\nSo the POC should avoid baking in an assumption that the local capture format is the final sharing format.\n\nA few other things I’d keep in mind:\n\n**1. Session Identity**\nWe probably want a GitButler-owned session id, not just:\n\n```text\n<agent>:<provider-session-key>\n```\n\nBecause handoff can become:\n\n```text\nGitButler session X\n  started from Claude transcript A\n  continued from OpenClaw transcript B\n  later appended Codex transcript C\n```\n\nThe provider session id is a source identifier, not necessarily the durable product/session identity.\n\n**2. Normalized Content**\nFor future handoff and website browsing, `source_record` is not enough. It is provenance. The useful product data is more like:\n\n```text\nrole\ncontent text\ntool call\ntool result\ndecision\nplan\nquestion\nanswer\nfile reference\ncommit/head reference\n```\n\nWe do not need all of that now, but the envelope should move toward “normalized conversation event plus original source record,” not “provider JSON with a few side fields.”\n\n**3. Repo State Anchors**\nSessions need anchors into repository history:\n\n```text\nstarting HEAD\ncurrent HEAD at capture\nbranch/stack if known\ndirty worktree summary maybe later\nPR/commit links later\n```\n\nFor handoff, this matters a lot. “Continue this session” without knowing what repo state the discussion referred to can get mushy fast.\n\n**4. Publish Boundary**\nFor colleague sharing, there should be an explicit action someday:\n\n```text\ncapture locally\nreview/redact/summarize\npublish/share session\nattach link to PR\n```\n\nI would be wary of automatic publishing. Agent transcripts are too likely to contain secrets, private paths, credentials, customer names, and half-formed thoughts.\n\n**5. Large Sessions**\nA single ordered list is fine for the POC. Long term, huge transcripts may want chunking or indexes. But I would not add that now. Just avoid a shape that makes chunking impossible later.\n\n**POC Direction**\nThe current POC is directionally fine if we treat it as:\n\n```text\nlocal raw capture substrate\n```\n\nThe next small alignment would be documenting a future split:\n\n```text\ndurable GitButler session id\nsource transcripts\nnormalized event envelopes\nlocal capture vs shareable export\nbranch/PR references to session ids\n```\n\nThat keeps today’s implementation small while making the path to both use cases much cleaner.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:05:22.403Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}